  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut the tofu into bite-sized cubes, then pat dry with kitchen paper to remove excess moisture. Add the garlic granules to a large bowl with the cornflour. Toss the tofu through until evenly coated, then shake off any excess."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Spray the tofu lightly with oil, then air fry at 180°C for 20 mins, shaking halfway through, until crispy and golden."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Wash the rice in cold water until it runs clear, then drain. Add to a saucepan with enough water to just cover it (roughly 1cm above the rice line). Bring to the boil over a medium-high heat, then cover with a lid and reduce the heat to low. Cook for 12 mins, then turn off the heat and leave to steam for another 5 mins. Fluff with a fork."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "While the rice cooks, peel and thinly slice the garlic, ginger and shallot. Trim and slice the spring onions into 3cm pieces, separating the white and green parts. Also, slice a few of the spring onion greens and the chillies for garnish and set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Place a large wok or frying pan over a medium heat. Add a drizzle of oil, then fry the garlic, ginger, shallot, most of the chillies and spring onion whites for 2 mins until fragrant."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Push the aromatics to the side to create a gap in the middle of the pan. Add the sugar and cook for 2-3 mins until it melts and turns a dark amber colour – keep an eye on it so it doesn’t burn."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour in the coconut water, soy sauce, white wine vinegar and white pepper. Let it bubble for another 2-3 mins until slightly thickened."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Toss in the crispy tofu and gently coat in the sauce until everything’s glossy and sticky."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve with the rice, then finish with the reserved spring onion greens, the rest of the chillies and any fresh herbs you fancy. Enjoy!"
    }
  ],
